    "This appears to be at odds with j i = 1 2 for all i, however one can interpret each Q(µ I) insertion as carrying a spin of j = -1.",
    "This is because, when acting upon the vertex operatorsV w i m i 1,m i 2, the operator U 0 determines m 1 -m 2, andQ(µ I) carries a U 0 charge of -1.This means that the constraint (3.15) is indeed satisfied if we extend it to include the spins of the N = 4 generators (in essence, we view the Q(µ I) as screening operators for U 0).",
